I"ƒ	<p>The <code>heatmiser</code> climate platform let you control <a href="https://www.heatmisershop.co.uk/room-thermostats/">Heatmiser DT/DT-E/PRT/PRT-E</a> thermostats from Heatmiser. The module itself is currently setup to work over a RS232 -&gt; RS485 converter, therefore it connects over IP.</p>
<p>Further work would be required to get this setup to connect over Wifi, but the HeatmiserV3 python module being used is a full implementation of the V3 protocol.</p>
<p>To set it up, add the following information to your <code>configuration.yaml</code> file:</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml">climate:
  - platform: heatmiser
    host: YOUR_IP_ADDRESS
    port: YOUR_PORT
    tstats:
      - id: THERMOSTAT_ID
        name: THERMOSTAT_NAME
</code></pre>
<p>A single interface can handle up to 32 connected devices.</p>
<div class="config-vars">
  <h3><a class="title-link" name="configuration-variables" href="#configuration-variables"></a> Configuration Variables</h3>
  <dl class=''><dt><a class='title-link' name='host' href='#host'></a> host</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>The IP address of your interface.</p>
</span></p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='port' href='#port'></a> port</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>The port that the interface is listening on.</p>
</span></p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='tstats' href='#tstats'></a> tstats</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='list'>list</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>A list of thermostats activated on the gateway.</p>
</span></p></dd><dd><dl class='nested'><dt><a class='title-link' name='id' href='#id'></a> id</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>The ID of the thermostat as configured on the device itself.</p>
</span></p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='name' href='#name'></a> name</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>A friendly name for the thermostat.</p>
</span></p></dd></dl></dd></dl>
</div>
